\q were divisions and debates.
\q
\v 16 Why did you lounge by shepherds’ cotes,
\q with only an ear for pastoral notes?
\q
\v 17 East of the Jordan the Gileadites stayed;
\q Dan held to his ships;
\q Asher sat still by the seaboard,
\q clinging to his creeks.
\q
\v 18 But Zebulun–the clan risked life and death
\q with Naphtali out in the open field!
\b
\q
\v 19 On came the kings, came at them,
\q Canaan’s kings came at them,
\q by Taănak, on Megiddo’s streams;
\q and much they made of it!
\q
